h3cDot11STATION.name: h3cDot11STATION

revisions.description: Add new node h3cDot11StationUpTimeTicks, h3cDot11StationSecIEStatus to h3cDot11StationAssociateTable.
Add new node h3cDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt and h3cDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt to h3cDot11StationStatisTable
Modified to add new trap and add h3cDot11StationRxNoise to h3cDot11StationAssociateTable.
The initial revision of this MIB module.

h3cDot11STATION.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
h3cDot11STATION.description: This MIB defines the configuration and statistic information of stations. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Control And Provisioning of Wireless Access Points Protocol The short name of protocol is CAPWAP. AC will control and manage AP by CAPWAP tunnel protocol defined by IETF. Also, a data tunnel will be set up between AC and AP. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associated with the AP. station (Client Station) A wireless device in a wireless network associated with an access point. MIC Message Integrity Check. A MIC can, optionally, be added to WEP-encrypted 802.11 frames. SSID Radio Service Set ID. It is used for identification during association. STA (WSTA) A non-AP 802.11 wireless station. WEP Wired Equivalent Privacy. 'WEP' is generally used to refer to 802.11 encryption. RSSI It is the received signal strength indication. It suggests the quality of received signal. RTS Request to Send, it is used to gain control of the medium for the transmission of 'large' frames, in which 'large' is defined by the RTS threshold in the network card driver. CTS Clear to Send, it is used to answer RTS frames. AKM The authentication and key management method defined by 802.11i, and which includes 802.1x and pre-shared key.

h3cDot11StationAssociateTable.name: h3cDot11StationAssociateTable
h3cDot11StationAssociateTable.description: This table contains the information of stations which are associating with the wireless network (current AC).

h3cDot11StationAssociateEntry.name: h3cDot11StationAssociateEntry
h3cDot11StationAssociateEntry.description: Each entry contains association information of each station.

h3cDot11StationMAC.name: h3cDot11StationMAC
h3cDot11StationMAC.description: Represents the unique MAC Address of station.

h3cDot11StationIPAddress.name: h3cDot11StationIPAddress
h3cDot11StationIPAddress.description: Represents the IP address of the station.

h3cDot11StationUserName.name: h3cDot11StationUserName
h3cDot11StationUserName.description: Represents the user name of the station.

h3cDot11StationTxRateSet.name: h3cDot11StationTxRateSet
h3cDot11StationTxRateSet.description: Represents the current transmit data rates for this station. Each byte will represent one rate. If the MSB(Most significant bit) is set, then this rate is a mandantory rate. Otherwise, it is optional.

h3cDot11StationUpTime.name: h3cDot11StationUpTime
h3cDot11StationUpTime.description: The time in seconds, how long this station has been associated with this device.

h3cDot11StationSignalStrength.name: h3cDot11StationSignalStrength
h3cDot11StationSignalStrength.description: Represents a device-dependent measure of the signal strength of latest packet received from this station.

h3cDot11StationRSSI.name: h3cDot11StationRSSI
h3cDot11StationRSSI.description: Represents a device-dependent measure of the RSSI. It is the received signal strength indication. The maximum value is defined by chip set vendors

h3cDot11StationChannel.name: h3cDot11StationChannel
h3cDot11StationChannel.description: Represents current radio channel used by station.

h3cDot11StationPowerSaveMode.name: h3cDot11StationPowerSaveMode
h3cDot11StationPowerSaveMode.description: Represents the power management mode of this station. The following values are supported: active(1) - This station is not in power-save mode and it is actively sending or receiving data. powersave(2) - This station is in power-save mode and it wakes up after sometime to check for buffer data.

h3cDot11StationAid.name: h3cDot11StationAid
h3cDot11StationAid.description: Represents the association identification number of station.

h3cDot11StationVlanId.name: h3cDot11StationVlanId
h3cDot11StationVlanId.description: Represents Vlan ID to which the station is associated.

h3cDot11StationAuthenMode.name: h3cDot11StationAuthenMode
h3cDot11StationAuthenMode.description: Represents the Authentication mode defined by 802.11.

h3cDot11StationAKMMode.name: h3cDot11StationAKMMode
h3cDot11StationAKMMode.description: Represents the key management mode defined by 802.11i.

h3cDot11StationSecurityCiphers.name: h3cDot11StationSecurityCiphers
h3cDot11StationSecurityCiphers.description: Represents the frame encryption cipher type used by station.

h3cDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode.name: h3cDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode
h3cDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode.description: Represents the encryption mode for this ESS.

h3cDot11StationRxSNR.name: h3cDot11StationRxSNR
h3cDot11StationRxSNR.description: Represents the signal and noise strength ratio of frame reception.

h3cDot11StationTxRate.name: h3cDot11StationTxRate
h3cDot11StationTxRate.description: Represents the transmission rate of frame.

h3cDot11StationRxRate.name: h3cDot11StationRxRate
h3cDot11StationRxRate.description: Represents the reception rate of frame.

h3cDot11StationVendorName.name: h3cDot11StationVendorName
h3cDot11StationVendorName.description: Represents the vendor name of the station.

h3cDot11StationRadioMode.name: h3cDot11StationRadioMode
h3cDot11StationRadioMode.description: Represents which radio type supported by the station. The WLAN system support the following possible radio types. dot11a(1), dot11b(2), dot11g(4), dot11n(8) For a station,it could support only one radio type at the same time.

h3cDot11StationRxNoise.name: h3cDot11StationRxNoise
h3cDot11StationRxNoise.description: Represents the received noise of the station.

h3cDot11StationTxSpeed.name: h3cDot11StationTxSpeed
h3cDot11StationTxSpeed.description: Represents the bytes of transmitted data frames to the station per second in sample interval.

h3cDot11StationRxSpeed.name: h3cDot11StationRxSpeed
h3cDot11StationRxSpeed.description: Represents the bytes of received data frames from the station per second in sample interval.

h3cDot11StationWmmMode.name: h3cDot11StationWmmMode
h3cDot11StationWmmMode.description: Represents the QoS mode of station. The following values are supported: wmm(1) - This QoS function is supported by this station. nonwmm(2) - This QoS function is not supported by this station.

h3cDot11StationSecIEStatus.name: h3cDot11StationSecIEStatus
h3cDot11StationSecIEStatus.description: Represents the security Information element for this station.

h3cDot11StationUpTimeTicks.name: h3cDot11StationUpTimeTicks
h3cDot11StationUpTimeTicks.description: Represents how long this station has been associated with this device.

h3cDot11StationRadioMode2.name: h3cDot11StationRadioMode2
h3cDot11StationRadioMode2.description: Represents which radio type supported by the station. The WLAN system support the following possible radio types. dot11a(1), dot11b(2), dot11g(4), dot11an(8), dot11gn(16) For a station,it could support only one radio type at the same time.

h3cDot11StationAssTime.name: h3cDot11StationAssTime
h3cDot11StationAssTime.description: Represents the time at which the station connected.

h3cDot11StationAPRelationTable.name: h3cDot11StationAPRelationTable
h3cDot11StationAPRelationTable.description: This table contains relation-ship between station, AP, Radio and WLANID, and the detailed information of station is kept in the h3cDot11StaAssociateTable table.

h3cDot11StationAPRelationEntry.name: h3cDot11StationAPRelationEntry
h3cDot11StationAPRelationEntry.description: Each entry contains relation-ship information with AP, Radio and WLANID of each station.

h3cDot11CurrAPID.name: h3cDot11CurrAPID
h3cDot11CurrAPID.description: To uniquely identify each AP, and relation-ship between h3cDot11CurrAPID and AP device will be static.

h3cDot11CurrWlanID.name: h3cDot11CurrWlanID
h3cDot11CurrWlanID.description: Represents WLAN ID of the BSS the station associated to.

h3cDot11StationStatisTable.name: h3cDot11StationStatisTable
h3cDot11StationStatisTable.description: This table contains statistics and status of all stations in the h3cDot11StaAssociateTable.

h3cDot11StationStatisEntry.name: h3cDot11StationStatisEntry
h3cDot11StationStatisEntry.description: This entry contains statistics and status for each station.

h3cDot11StationRxFrameCnt.name: h3cDot11StationRxFrameCnt
h3cDot11StationRxFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are received by AP from station.

h3cDot11StationTxFrameCnt.name: h3cDot11StationTxFrameCnt
h3cDot11StationTxFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are sent to station from AP.

h3cDot11StationDropFrameCnt.name: h3cDot11StationDropFrameCnt
h3cDot11StationDropFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are dropped.

h3cDot11StationRxFrameBytes.name: h3cDot11StationRxFrameBytes
h3cDot11StationRxFrameBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are received by AP from station.

h3cDot11StationTxFrameBytes.name: h3cDot11StationTxFrameBytes
h3cDot11StationTxFrameBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are sent to station from AP.

h3cDot11StationDropFrameBytes.name: h3cDot11StationDropFrameBytes
h3cDot11StationDropFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes are dropped.

h3cDot11StationRxRetryPkts.name: h3cDot11StationRxRetryPkts
h3cDot11StationRxRetryPkts.description: Represents the count of frames that are retransmitted to AP from station.

h3cDot11StationTxRetryPkts.name: h3cDot11StationTxRetryPkts
h3cDot11StationTxRetryPkts.description: Represents the count of frames that are retransmitted to station from AP.

h3cDot11StationRxRetryBytes.name: h3cDot11StationRxRetryBytes
h3cDot11StationRxRetryBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are retransmitted to AP from station.

h3cDot11StationTxRetryBytes.name: h3cDot11StationTxRetryBytes
h3cDot11StationTxRetryBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are retransmitted to station from AP.

h3cDot11StationThroughput.name: h3cDot11StationThroughput
h3cDot11StationThroughput.description: Represents how many payload bytes of data frame are sent and received by station.

h3cDot11StationSuccessTxCnt.name: h3cDot11StationSuccessTxCnt
h3cDot11StationSuccessTxCnt.description: Represents how many frames have been successfully sent to station.

h3cDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt.name: h3cDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt
h3cDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been successfully sent to station.

h3cDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt.name: h3cDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt
h3cDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been received from station.

h3cDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt.name: h3cDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt
h3cDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been sent to station.

h3cDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes.name: h3cDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes
h3cDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes of data frames have been received from station.

h3cDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes.name: h3cDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes
h3cDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes of data frames have been sent to station.

h3cDot11StationRxFragCnt.name: h3cDot11StationRxFragCnt
h3cDot11StationRxFragCnt.description: Represents the number of fragmented data frames that received from station.

h3cDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt.name: h3cDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt
h3cDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of error data frames that are received by AP from station.

h3cDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt.name: h3cDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt
h3cDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of data frames that are retransmitted to station from AP.

h3cDot11StaTxDataRatePkts.name: h3cDot11StaTxDataRatePkts
h3cDot11StaTxDataRatePkts.description: Represents how many data frames of each rate have been received from station.

h3cDot11StaRxDataRatePkts.name: h3cDot11StaRxDataRatePkts
h3cDot11StaRxDataRatePkts.description: Represents how many data frames of each rate have been sent to station.

h3cDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts.name: h3cDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts
h3cDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts.description: Represents how many data frames of different signal strength have been received from station.

h3cDot11StationMICErrorTrap.name: h3cDot11StationMICErrorTrap
h3cDot11StationMICErrorTrap.description: This notification is to indicate the occurrence of a MIC failure in a certain station.

h3cDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap.name: h3cDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap
h3cDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap.description: This notification is to indicate which station happened authentication failure.

h3cDot11StationAuthorFailTrap.name: h3cDot11StationAuthorFailTrap
h3cDot11StationAuthorFailTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station authorization fails.

h3cDot11StationAssocFailTrap.name: h3cDot11StationAssocFailTrap
h3cDot11StationAssocFailTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station association fails.

h3cDot11StationDeAssocTrap.name: h3cDot11StationDeAssocTrap
h3cDot11StationDeAssocTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station de-association occurred.

h3cDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap.name: h3cDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap
h3cDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap.description: This trap is sent when a station is authorized successfully.

h3cDot11StationRoamingTrap.name: h3cDot11StationRoamingTrap
h3cDot11StationRoamingTrap.description: This trap is sent when a station roamed successfully.

h3cDot11StationDisconnectTrap.name: h3cDot11StationDisconnectTrap
h3cDot11StationDisconnectTrap.description: This notification is sent when station disconnects with AP.

h3cDot11UserDisconnectTrap.name: h3cDot11UserDisconnectTrap
h3cDot11UserDisconnectTrap.description: This notification is sent when user disconnects with AP.

h3cDot11StationTrapBSSID.name: h3cDot11StationTrapBSSID
h3cDot11StationTrapBSSID.description: Represents on which BSSID of AP the event happened.

h3cDot11StationTrapStaMAC.name: h3cDot11StationTrapStaMAC
h3cDot11StationTrapStaMAC.description: Represents the MAC address of station which happened message integrity check (MIC) errors.

h3cDot11StationSessionStartTime.name: h3cDot11StationSessionStartTime
h3cDot11StationSessionStartTime.description: Represents the time at which the station connected.

h3cDot11StationAssocFailCause.name: h3cDot11StationAssocFailCause
h3cDot11StationAssocFailCause.description: Represents the cause of the station association failure.

h3cDot11StationAuthorFailCause.name: h3cDot11StationAuthorFailCause
h3cDot11StationAuthorFailCause.description: Represents the cause of the station authorization failure.

h3cDot11StationFailCauseDesc.name: h3cDot11StationFailCauseDesc
h3cDot11StationFailCauseDesc.description: Represents the failure description of the station.

h3cDot11StationSessionDuration.name: h3cDot11StationSessionDuration
h3cDot11StationSessionDuration.description: Represents the duration of the station sesssion.

h3cDot11StationRoamingTime.name: h3cDot11StationRoamingTime
h3cDot11StationRoamingTime.description: Represents the time at which the station roamed.

h3cDot11StationACIPAddress.name: h3cDot11StationACIPAddress
h3cDot11StationACIPAddress.description: For roam-in station, it represents the ip address of home AC. For roam-out station, it represents the ip address of foreign AC.

h3cDot11StationAPName.name: h3cDot11StationAPName
h3cDot11StationAPName.description: Name of the AP which the station connects to.

h3cDot11StationBSSID.name: h3cDot11StationBSSID
h3cDot11StationBSSID.description: BSSID which the station connects to.

h3cDot11StaDisconnectReason.name: h3cDot11StaDisconnectReason
h3cDot11StaDisconnectReason.description: Reason why the station disconnects with the AP.

h3cDot11StationACIPv6Add.name: h3cDot11StationACIPv6Add
h3cDot11StationACIPv6Add.description: For roam-in station, it represents the IPv6 address of home AC. For roam-out station, it represents the IPv6 address of foreign AC.
